Span.Text: In-vehicle and hand-held mobile devices, enabled with apps and cloud services, help first responders to gather and upload information digitally (e.g., images, video, and audio files) to provide a first-hand perspective from the scene of an event or emergency. With security-enhanced mobile connections to the agency network or command centre, the digital files can be quickly reviewed to help improve citizen safety and agency response. Real-time communication helps mobile police, first responders and colleagues collaborate to make timely, informed decisions from virtually anywhere, anytime.
Design data-driven response plans to educate citizens, prepare for disasters.
Capture all disaster information in a single, integrated solution for better  end-to-end management.
Inspect public buildings to ensure they meet fire codes and other regulations.
